Its pretty bad when I can say that Monster hunter has better general input controls that this game-- and I HATE Monster Hunter (EDIT: older MH Games) because of how it does gear loot and weapon locking.

Not even fighting games have this type of input control shit in it... Basically-- you have to be NEAR perfect on all button press' to not experience Phantom inputs... But also, fucking dodge in this game goes off AFTER BUTTON LIFT because its tied to fucking SPRINT.

Also, input loading is just bad design; phantom inputs are a thing. 

I am in mid swing, get hit thus plays the hit animation so I switch to slamming the dodge button... BUT the character attacks because its still has the attack press loaded from before the hit is poor design.

My issues arent even to the difficulty or the exploration. Basic QoL stuff that needs to be in this type of game to not rely on some fucking wiki for EVERYTHING. BoTW does the same shiz of giving you little to nothing like Elden-- but it had a fucking Journal.

I know people are going to give me shit for giving Elden a  7 and not higher, but remember; this is coming from someone coming in this never playing a Souls game before nor has some type of "Souls Boner" for it-- ignoring actual improvements that could be made.

@Milkosrs Those were all Linear with no where near as half of the locations as this game has-- its massive and a lot of shit to do. I have like 3 side quests-- 1 which is VITAL to the story apparently that I remember 0 bit of info over and I HATE having to look any of this up...

I get that some will say "ThAt MaKeS iT dArK SoUlS"-- it makes it outdated. You have an open world with multiple NPCs that have unrepeatable info. I shouldn't need a fucking wiki open to know shit. Destiny got bashed for doing this for their game-- I'm going to do it here too.

Biggest prob that 100% knocks at least 2 points off of my score is how NPCs are handled-- The lack of any type of journal system to keep track of their tasks.

And I dont think I am asking for much for a literal journal with basic info given my NPCs that some never gets repeated.

Part of me wants to do a Elden Ring review-- tho, I haven't beaten it yet but I'm getting there... I think...

But given how the community around it sends death threats to negativity (literal bomb threat to the Ubisoft guy...) I will just say the game is a 7/10 and not a 10.

Is it challenging? Sure, but if you level long enough and boost the power of your weapon, you can seriously rip through shiz pretty well. Just don't run in like a headless chicken and watch the AI. Open world fights alone can be cheesed using the horse.

@PjCFrink92 @JaxonKEKW @shamwow0098 @nintendolife It all depends on laws that each country has over protections-- however saves themselves dont really hit Copyright laws because of games in general all having... @PjCFrink92 @JaxonKEKW @shamwow0098 @nintendolife However if we go to the US side of things; take my hypothetical; Gamestop sells me a used DS game that has been hack to include items not possible or in amount that isnt realistic. @PjCFrink92 @JaxonKEKW @shamwow0098 @nintendolife Copyright & IP Violations are in fact very different. One has to do w/ use of a material VS claiming a material and selling it as your own-- at least on the fundamental level. Depending on the country (Japan) IP Violations tend to count mods/hacks but not exactly due to property.

@PjCFrink92 @JaxonKEKW @shamwow0098 @nintendolife If game saves were copyrighted materials, no game could effectively use it without paying royalties to someone for a basic system every game use. Effectively it's a free resource or even an open concept. Laws to hit this would be because the product or IP was modified and sold.

@PjCFrink92 @JaxonKEKW @shamwow0098 @nintendolife Effectively, they modified a protected product and tired to sell it. JPs laws over IP are far different than the US or even EU.
